  "body": "Closeout memo for the 2026-05-24 oagp-strategist working session that began 2026-05-23 with seat staffing under Director direction and continued through 2026-05-24 with v0.1.2 ship-and-validate. Substantive arc: (1) /oagp-onboard read of substrate; PO authorized seat staffing. (2) Drafted v0.1.1 staffing reflection + canonical promotion of /oagp-bootstrap + /oagp-onboard as adoption-cycle primitives. (3) Read three new morning memos (0900 SCHEMA v1.1.0 ship FYI + canonical-orgs library residence coordination request from orgdef-strategist; 0905 cross-machine skill deployment friction empirical signal; 1500 thingalog-to-oagp-lineage observation from thingalog-strategist). (4) On PO direction 'tying to thingalog makes no sense', drafted v0.1.2 omnibus: canonical adoption-cycle skill distribution v0.1 (residence migration to oagp-org/skills/, install scripts at install/install-claude-code-skills.{ps1,sh}, README Quick install section, cross-spec coordination memo to thingalog-strategist proposing thingalog/skills/ deprecation timeline) + canonical promotion of /oagp-closeout (session-cycle closing skill; transcript-position-tag convention canonically encoded in Phase 2 table, resolving queue item 2 for the canonical case). (5) Committed and pushed v0.1.1 + v0.1.2 bundle as 46e9312. (6) PO ran install on second machine via bash: 'very low-friction' — empirical validation of v0.1 distribution. (7) PO ran install on primary machine via PowerShell 5.1: parser error at line 47. Root cause: em-dashes in .ps1 read as Windows-1252 smart-quotes without UTF-8 BOM. Fixed in be146ce; PO re-ran; same error from a third em-dash on a Write-Warning line I missed. Fixed in bd2d3b9 (verified ASCII-only via byte-scan). (8) PO confirmed install works on primary machine. (9) PO invoked /oagp-closeout in the same session that authored it — recursive empirical validation. Queue state after this session: items 1 (adoption-cycle canonical-promotion) and 2 (transcript-tagging convention) resolved; items 6 (plugin packaging) and 7 (cross-runtime delivery) partially addressed by v0.1 distribution with v0.2 (substrate-neutral primer URL) and v0.3 (Claude Code plugin packaging) explicitly scheduled in cross-vendor-red-line-respecting order; items 3 (org-state-fork-for-time-travel pattern-promotion), 4 (async-organization positioning), 5 (Caliper local-conventions canonical work), 8 (oagp.org canonical hosting) remain open. Pending action-required memos to this seat: 2026-05-23-1600 (bind/agent-sdk graduation, thingalog-strategist), 2026-05-24-0900 (canonical-orgs library residence coordination, orgdef-strategist — reply still owed), 2026-05-24-1500 (thingalog-to-oagp lineage observation, thingalog-strategist — observation only). Side-effect strategist learning worth flagging for the next incumbent: PowerShell 5.1 reads .ps1 files as ANSI/Windows-1252 absent a UTF-8 BOM, which turns UTF-8 em-dashes into smart-quote terminators. ASCII-only content in install scripts is the simplest defense; if future contributors need non-ASCII, add a UTF-8 BOM. Side-effect substrate-validation worth recording: the canonical-skill-distribution-via-junction-symlink pattern works cross-machine (Windows + bash) with one-command install and zero meta-research. Adoption-barrier-collapse argument for canonicalization is no longer theoretical.",
